'''Jerca Vodušek Starič''' (born 1950) is a [[Slovenes|Slovene]] [[historian]]. She received a bachelor's degree in history at the Faculty of Arts of the [[University of Ljubljana]], a master's degree in 1979, and a PhD in 1991.

Her field of expertise is [[Slovenes|Slovene]] and [[Europe]]an history. Her focus is the government takeover by the communists in [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]] after [[World War II]]. Currently she is a professor of modern history at the [http://www.ff.uni-mb.si/?language_id=1 Faculty of Arts] in [[Maribor]]. From 2005-08, she was the director of the [http://euparl.net/9353000/1/j9vvhskmycle0vf/vhssltvsfjwz Institute of Contemporary History] in [[Ljubljana]].

