{{Infobox person |name = Dr. Mu-Kien Adriana Sang |image = Replace this image female.svg |caption = |image_size = |module = {{Infobox officeholder |embed = yes | office = [[Chairperson]] of the [[Dominican Academy of History]] | term_start = 13 July 2016 | term_end = | deputy = [[Adriano Miguel Tejada]] | predecessor = [[Bernardo Vega]] | successor = | office2 = [[Vice-chairperson]] of the [[Dominican Academy of History]] | term_start2 = 1 August 2013 | term_end2 = 13 July 2016 | predecessor2 = [[Bernardo Vega]] | successor2 = [[Adriano Miguel Tejada]] }} |module2 = {{Infobox writer |embed = yes |name = |native_name = Mu-Kien Adriana Sang Ben |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1955|9|8}} |birth_place = {{Flagicon|DOM}} [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], [[Dominican Republic]] |death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |death_place = |resting_place = |pseudonym = |occupation = Historian, essayist, analyst, politologist and academic |nationality = Dominican |period = |language = Spanish |genre = [[History]], [[Biographic]] |subject = |movement = |notableworks = "Ulises Heureaux: Biografía de un Dictador"; "Buenaventura Báez: El Caudillo del Sur (1844-1878)"; "Una Utopía Inconclusa: Espaillat y el Liberalismo Dominicano del Siglo XIX"; "Historia Dominicana: Ayer y Hoy" |awards = Premio Nacional de Didáctica (2000); Premio Nacional de Historia (2001) |spouse = [[Rafael Toribio]] |partner = |children = |relatives = Miguel Sang, Ana Ben(parents) |signature = |signature_alt = |website = {{URL|linkedin.com/pub/mu-kien-adriana-sang-ben-de-toribio/4a/700/1a}} |portaldisp = }} }} '''Mu-Kien Adriana Sang Ben''' (born [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], 1955) is a historian, essayist, analyst, political scientist and academic from the [[Dominican Republic]]. Sang is Vice-Rector of the [[Pontifical Catholic University Mother and Teacher]].<ref name=Hoy>{{cite web|author1=Fernardo Quiroz|title=María Isabel Soldevila a los 29 años de edad dirige Escuela Comunicación PUCMM|url=http://hoy.com.do/maria-isabel-soldevila-a-los-29-anosde-edad-dirige-escuela-comunicacion-pucmm/|publisher=[[Hoy (Dominican newspaper)|Hoy]]|accessdate=25 July 2014|language=Spanish|date=31 March 2007|quote=[[María Isabel Soldevila|Soldevila]] resaltó el apoyo que ha dado el rector de la PUCMM, monseñor [[Agripino Núñez Collado]], y la vicerrectora académica, Mu-Kien Adriana Sang, a la Escuela de Comunicación.}}</ref>
The daughter of a [[Cantonese people|Cantonese]] immigrant man, and a Dominican-born woman whose father was a [[Ethnic Chinese in the Dominican Republic|Chinese immigrant]] and her mother was [[Mulatto]] (of African and European descent).<ref>{{cite news |title=¡Uy! ¡Qué miedo, me salvé! |url=http://hoy.com.do/uy-que-miedo-salve/ |publisher=Hoy |date= 5 October 2013 |accessdate=4 November 2013 |quote=La polémica sentencia del Tribunal Constitucional promulgada hace unos días ha provocado encendidas reacciones; más en contra que a favor. (...) No me había sentido aludida con el contenido de la famosa sentencia 168/13 del 25 de septiembre de 2013. (...) Mi madre, Ana Ben Rodríguez de Sang, era una hermosa domínico-china, hija de una mulata, Andrea Rodríguez, y un chino, Ventura Ben.|language=es}}</ref> Sang has a degree in Teaching ''Summa Cum Laude'' in the ''[[Pontificia Universidad Católica Madre y Maestra]]'', where she has taught for more than two decades. She did her graduate degree in Adult Education in the ''[[Centro de Cooperación Regional para la Educación de Adultos de América Latina y el Caribe]]'' (CREFAL) in 1978, in [[Mexico City]]. In 1985 he achieved his PhD in History and Civilization at the ''[[School for Advanced Studies in the Social Sciences]]'' in [[Paris]]. She translated from French to Spanish the work ''Correspondence of the Consul of France in Santo Domingo'', published in two volumes under the sponsorship of the official Sesquicentennial Commission of National Independence. She has been a guest professor and public speaker at several universities in different nations.
In 2006, a street was named in her honor at the [[Plaza of Culture Juan Pablo Duarte]], host of the [[International Book Fair of Santo Domingo]].<ref name=9naFeriaLibro>{{cite news |title=Homenajean a la historiadora Mu-Kien Sang Ben |url=http://www.hoy.com.do/el-pais/2006/5/8/179698/ |publisher=Hoy |date=8 May 2006 |accessdate=22 June 2013 |language=es |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130624084340/http://www.hoy.com.do/el-pais/2006/5/8/179698/ |archivedate=24 June 2013 |df= }}</ref>
Her husband, [[Rafael Toribio]], has been rector of the [[Instituto Tecnológico de Santo Domingo|Technological Institute of Santo Domingo]] (INTEC).
